Steve Francia joins Google
17 Sep 2016
Tags: Google, @spf13

Guillaume Laforge

* Summary

On his blog, the well-known contributor to the Go ecosystem Steve Francia announces he's joined Google.
After working at Mongo and Docker, Steve joins the Go language team at Google with the role to improve the Go user and developer experience.
Steve created the [[https://gohugo.io/][Hugo]] static website generator, 
the [[https://github.com/spf13/viper][Viper]] 
and [[https://github.com/spf13/cobra][Cobra]] libraries, 
and contributed articles, presentations, to the Go ecosystem,
as well as organizing the GothamGo conference.

